TY  - JOUR
AU  - Rob, Rafael
T1  - Entry, Fixed Costs and the Aggregation of Private Information
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297485
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 4
SP  - 619
EP  - 630
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We investigate the ability of the price system to aggregate private information in a market of uncertain size and where set-up costs are incurred by entrants. It is shown that the equilibrium is random even when the totality of private information is so large that aggregate uncertainty is virtually non-existent. In particular, the limiting equilibrium does not approach the full-information, Walrasian outcome. Hence, the model identifies a technological factor (increasing returns) which gives rise to informational losses.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297485
ER  - 



