TY  - JOUR
AU  - Fudenberg, Drew
AU  - Kreps, David M.
T1  - Reputation in the Simultaneous Play of Multiple Opponents
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297482
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 4
SP  - 541
EP  - 568
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Imagine that one player, the “incumbent” competes with several “entrants”. Each entrant competes only with the incumbent, but observes play in all contests. Previous work shows that, as more and more entrants are added, the incumbent's reputation may dominate play of the game, if the entrants are faced in sequence. We identify conditions under which similar results obtain when the entrants are faced simultaneously, and we find specifications in which adding more simultaneous entrants has a dramatically different effect. We also show that, with either sequential or simultaneous play, incumbents need not prefer the situation in which their reputations can and do dominate play to the “informationally isolated” case in which each entrant observes only play in its own contest.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297482
ER  - 



