TY  - JOUR
AU  - Kolstad, Charles D.
AU  - Mathiesen, Lars
T1  - Necessary and Sufficient Conditions for Uniqueness of a Cournot Equilibrium
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297489
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 4
SP  - 681
EP  - 690
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - In this paper a theorem is developed giving necessary and sufficient conditions for the uniqueness of homogeneous product Cournot equilibria. The result appears to be the strongest to date and the first to involve both necessity and sufficiency. The theorem states than an equilibrium is unique if and only if the determinant of the Jacobian of marginal profits for firms producing positive output is positive at all equilibria. The result applies to the case where profit functions are twice differentiable and pseudoconcave, industry output can be bounded, the above Jacobian is non-singular at equilibria, and marginal profits are strictly negative for non-producing firms. The proof uses fixed point index theory from differential topology.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297489
ER  - 



